# E2E + Railway Workflow

After **any auth, API, or deploy-related change**, run E2E before marking complete.

## Required verification loop

```text
Change code
  → pnpm build
  → pnpm --filter @genie/e2e test   (or smoke + auth-api minimum)
  → fix failures
  → re-test
  → push
  → confirm Railway CORS_ORIGINS + Supabase URLs for production
```

## Minimum test command

```bash
pnpm build
pnpm --filter @genie/e2e exec playwright test tests/smoke.spec.ts tests/auth-guards.spec.ts tests/auth-api.spec.ts
```

## Production auth (Railway)

When frontend domain changes, update Railway:

```text
CORS_ORIGINS=https://<vercel-domain>,http://localhost:3000
```

See `docs/deployment/AUTH_DEPLOY_CHECKLIST.md`.

## Do not mark auth work complete without

- [ ] E2E smoke + auth-guards pass
- [ ] E2E auth-api pass (onboard → session → me)
- [ ] E2E auth-flow pass when Supabase secrets available
- [ ] Railway CORS documented/updated for live domain
